latestIgtvVideos.title: Virtual dinner date with @arjunkapoor to help with #Covid19 relief
latestIgtvVideos.caption: With the help of @give_india, we at @fankindofficial and @arjunkapoor have come together to help provide cash in hand to daily wage workers who have lost their livelihood due to the lockdown. This is our opportunity to truly help those less fortunate than us. 100% of your donation will go to the daily wager workers. GiveIndia has identified more than 60 thousand families that need our help. So please open your hearts and donate as much as you can. And my super awesome brother will virtually hang out with 5 lucky winners who donate with a very entertaining dinner on Saturday night. Trust me, he is the funniest person to hangout with - I have this on good authority coz he’s my daily dose of laughter hehe.. and you’ll can do this from the comfort of your own home! Video chat zindabad! So pls log on to fankind.org/arjun & donate! (Link in bio) #FankindXArjun #Covid19

latestPosts.caption:
The 30s Club | Is this the decade we finally take control of our money? 💸 

If you’re in your 30s and have Googled, “How much should I have saved by now?” - I’ve been there too. Confused, stressed, and honestly just winging it most days. 

One thing I wish someone had told me when I was a wide eyed 21 year old holding my first pay check: income does not equal wealth! And saving is not the same as building.

3 money mistakes I regret making:
🫣 Just saving and thinking that’s enough
🫣 putting off investing because it felt “too complicated”
🫣 Not having a safety net

If you’re still figuring things out or finding your way toward your financial future - you’re not late, you’re just in the 30s Club. We ask questions, we learn & we unlearn! We take action & we grow. Financially & otherwise. 

{The 30s Club, Financial Freedom, Women and Money, Investing, Financial Growth}

We never know what someone’s body is surviving.

That weight gain or loss? 
It could be from heartbreak, grief, stress, mental health struggles, or even a chronic illness.

You don’t know what they’re dealing with, so why add to the weight or be a trigger? 

And really though, someone else’s body is not yours to pass judgment on ❌

So here’s a radical idea: Just don’t comment.

#ChooseKindness

Introducing: The 30s Club 🌀

A series for all the in-between thoughts that we don’t say out loud: the spirals, the doubts, the late-night existential scrolls! 

And the first one had to be about that weird stuck feeling - when everyone around you seems to be moving forward. Weddings, babies, investments… and I’m just here wondering if I even have the right boxes, let alone ticking them.

That’s really how 30s Club was born: not with answers, but with honesty. A little space for comfort. For saying the things we usually keep to ourselves.

So if you’ve been feeling it too, come hang in the comments? Maybe we’ll feel a little less alone in it together 🫶🏽
